.TH _PRINTF 3 "November 22, 2025" "_printf Manual pages" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of printf with basic format specifiers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string and a variable number of arguments.
Output is written to the standard output stream
.BR stdout .

The
.I format
string is composed of ordinary characters (which are copied unchanged to the output stream)
and conversion specifiers, each introduced by the '%' character.

This simplified version of
.B printf
supports the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string of characters. If the string pointer is NULL, the string "(null)" is printed.

.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed integer using the helper function
.BR print_int() .

.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal '%' character.

.TP
Any other character following '%'
is printed literally, preceded by '%'.

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success,
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed (excluding the terminating null byte).
On error (such as a NULL format string or an incomplete format specifier at the end),
.B -1
is returned.

.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B -1
Returned if
.I format
is NULL or if a '%' is followed by the end of the string.

.SH NOTES
This implementation does not handle:
.IP 

\[bu] 2
Buffering optimizations of the standard C library
.IP 

\[bu] 2
Flag characters
.IP 

\[bu] 2
Field width
.IP 

\[bu] 2
Precision
.IP 

\[bu] 2
Length modifiers

It is intended as a learning exercise to mimic the behavior of
.BR printf (3)
with limited functionality.

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
_printf("Hello %s! Number: %d%%\\n", "World", 42);
.fi
This prints:
.nf
Hello World! Number: 42%
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR putchar (3)

.SH AUTHORS Johnson A Martinez, Eloy A. Alicea and Eugenio Martinez.


